### RazorForge Viewed[T] - Scoped read-only access token
###
### Viewed[T] is created ONLY by the `viewing` syntax, NOT by creators.
### It provides read-only access to entities/residents within a scoped block.
###
### Syntax:
###   using <entity_or_resident>.view() as v
###     show(v.member variable)  # Read-only access
###     var copy = v   # OK - Viewed can be copied
###   # v destroyed here, cannot escape scope
###
### Properties:
### - Created by compiler via `viewing` syntax
### - Scope-bound: cannot be stored, returned, or escape
### - Copyable: multiple Viewed[T] handles can coexist
### - Read-only: cannot modify through this handle
### - Temporary: source is invalidated during scope, restored on exit
### - Single-threaded: for multi-threaded use, see Inspected[T]
###
### This type is a marker for the type system - the compiler handles all operations.
module Core

@llvm("ptr")
record Viewed[T]
  pass

routine T.view() -> Viewed[T]
  return Viewed[T](me.snatch())

# NOTE: No creators, no manual methods - all operations handled by compiler
# The address member variable is managed internally by the viewing syntax implementation
# Users should NEVER create Viewed[T] values directly

# ============================================================================
# Resource management — enables `using entity.view() as v`
# ============================================================================

routine Viewed[T].$enter()
  return

routine Viewed[T].$exit()
  return

# ============================================================================
# Display (transparent - delegates to inner value)
# ============================================================================

@readonly
routine Viewed[T].$represent() -> Text
  danger!
    var snatched = Snatched[T](me)
    return snatched.read().$represent()

@readonly
routine Viewed[T].$diagnose() -> Text
  danger!
    var snatched = Snatched[T](me)
    return me.type_name() + "(" + snatched.read().$diagnose() + ")"
